Ephraim Makgoba, Judge President of the Limpopo Division of the High Court of South Africa sworn in Azwindini Jerry Ndou as the acting Premier of the province on Monday morning. Ndou, MEC for the Department of Public Works, Roads and Infrastructure will act while Premier Stan Mathabatha is on leave for a week a press statement issued on Monday by the Premier s Spokesperson, Kenny Mathivha informed. Story: NELIE ERASMUS &gt;&gt;nelie.observer@gmail.com Featured photo: Acting Premier Jerry Ndou.